            07/10/17 10:12 AM EDT
        



Pre-Market Technical Recap on Wireless Communications Stocks -- Vodafone, xG Technology, NII Holdings, and Telefonica Brasil
PR Newswire






NEW YORK, July 10, 2017


 NEW YORK, July 10, 2017 /PRNewswire/ --
If you want a Stock Review on VOD, XGTI, NIHD or VIV then come over to http://dailystocktracker.com/register/ and sign up for your free customized report today. This morning's research on DailyStockTracker.com is focused on the Wireless Communications space, which consists of companies engaged in providing wireless communication services, such as paging, cell phone, and other satellite telecommunication services. Under review today are the following equities: Vodafone Group PLC (NASDAQ: VOD), xG Technology Inc. (NASDAQ: XGTI), NII Holdings Inc. (NASDAQ: NIHD), and Telefonica Brasil S.A. (NYSE: VIV). Daily Stock Tracker provides great insights on these stocks in its free research reports at:
 http://dailystocktracker.com/register/ 
 Vodafone 
Shares in Newbury, the UK-based Vodafone Group PLC ended Friday's session 0.39% higher at $28.68 with a total trading volume of 2.13 million shares. The stock has advanced 11.12% over the previous three months and 17.40% on an YTD basis. The Company's shares are trading 0.71% above their 50-day moving average and 7.24% above their 200-day moving average. Moreover, shares of Vodafone, which provides mobile communications services in Europe, Middle-East, Africa, Asia/Pacific, and the US, have a Relative Strength Index (RSI) of 52.03.  
On June 12 th, 2017, research firm Argus upgraded the Company's stock rating from 'Hold' to 'Buy'.
On June 20 th, 2017, Vodafone announced that it is working with Smart Meter LLC, a mobile health services provider for diabetes management, to bring reliable and efficient accessibility to its customers around the world. Smart Meter's iGlucose platform will benefit from Vodafone's global Internet of Things network to address customer demand in more than 160 countries. Free research report on VOD is available at:
 http://dailystocktracker.com/registration/?symbol=VOD 
  xG Technology 
 Sarasota, Florida headquartered xG Technology Inc.'s shares saw a slight drop of 0.60%, closing the day at $1.66. A total volume of 94,658 shares was traded. The stock has advanced 12.16% in the previous three months and 22.96% on an YTD basis. The Company's shares are trading 2.80% below their 50-day moving average. Additionally, shares of xG Technology, which designs, develops, and delivers advanced wireless communications solutions worldwide, have an RSI of 45.66.
On June 26 th, 2017, xG Technology announced that it is aware of a press release issued by Purcell Julie & Lefkowitz, LLP claiming an alleged potential breach of fiduciary duty involving the Company's board of directors. The Company has received no communication of any kind from this firm regarding such a claim. Moreover, no such claim or allegation has been made by any shareholders or regulatory body.  The complimentary research report on XGTI can be downloaded at:
