NII Holdings, Inc. (NASDAQ:NIHD) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume 












































 Finance DailyDaily markets, commodities, personal finance and economic newsNII Holdings, Inc. (NASDAQ:NIHD) Experiences Lighter than Usual Trading Volume
July 18, 2017 By Ted Blackburn Tweet
        Advertisement



NII Holdings, Inc. shares had a trading volume of 921K in the last trading session.  Shares saw a steep decrease in trading volume of 76.09% under the normal average daily volume. 
 Short traders are feeling a little more bearish of late if you consider the rise in short interest.  The stock realized a rise in short interest of 19.56% between June 15, 2017 and May 31, 2017.  Short shares increased 1,261,474 over that period.  With short interest at 7,710,484 and short average daily volume at 3,675,164, days to cover is 2.1 and the percentage of shorted shares was 0.08% on May 31. 
 The following firms have also recently changed their position in NIHD.   As of quarter end Meeder Asset Management Inc had acquired 1,625 shares growing its position 759.3%. The value of the total investment in NII Holdings, Inc. increased from $0 to $1,000 a change of inf% since the last quarter. As of the end of the quarter Nomura Asset Management Co Ltd had sold  a total of 190 shares trimming its stake by 0.0%. The value of the investment in NII Holdings, Inc. went from $1,232,000 to $593,000 decreasing 51.9% for the reporting period.
 As of the end of the quarter Morgan Stanley had acquired 180,449 shares growing its holdings by 115.8%. The value of the company’s investment in NII Holdings, Inc. went from $335,000 to $437,000 a change of $102,000 quarter over quarter. Goldman Sachs Group Inc divested its ownership by selling 52,364 shares a decrease of 76.8% in the quarter. Goldman Sachs Group Inc currently owns 15,820 shares with a value of $21,000. The value of the position overall is down by 85.7%.        Advertisement






  November 23 investment analysts at Jefferies maintained a company rating of “Underweight” and lowered the price expectation  to $1.50 from $4.50. Jefferies began coverage of the stock setting a rating of “Underperform” and establishing a price target of $4.50.
 On April 29 Citigroup held the company rating at “Sell” but lowered the price expectation from $2.00 to $0.70. April 11 investment analysts at Barclays left the company rating at “Underweight” but moved down the price target  to $0.50 from $2.50.
 On March 20, 2014 the stock rating was changed to a “Market Perform” according to a Wells Fargo report a cut from the previous “Outperform” rating. On March 3 the stock rating was downgraded to “Hold” from “Buy” in a statement from Gabelli & Co..
 The company is now down since yesterday’s close of $0.6.  Company shares last traded at $0.569 just below the 50 day moving average of $0.64 and which is just a bit below the 200 day moving average of $1.52.  The 50 day moving average moved down $-0.07 and the 200 day average was down $-0.94. 
 NII Holdings, Inc., launched on October 18, 2000, is a holding company. The Company operates through its subsidiary, Nextel Telecomunicacoes Ltda. (Nextel Brazil). The Company provides wireless communication services under the Nextel brand in Brazil with its principal operations located in urban and suburban centers with population densities and related transportation corridors of that country, including Rio de Janeiro and Sao Paulo. The Company operates in the Nextel Brazil segment. It also offers long-term evolution (LTE) services in Rio de Janeiro and provides services on its integrated digital enhanced network (iDEN) network throughout various regions in Brazil. The iDEN technology is a digital technology that is able to operate on non-contiguous spectrum frequencies..
