NIHD - Market Data & News
NIHD - Stock Valuation Report
 Trade 
NII Holdings Inc. (NIHD) had a rough trading day for Friday July 14 as 
shares 
tumbled 5.86%, or a loss of $-0.0369 per share, to close at $0.59. After opening the day at $0.63, shares of NII Holdings Inc. traded as high as $0.66 and as 
low as $0.56. Volume was 1.29 million shares over 2,414 trades, against an average daily volume of 1.87 million shares and a total float of 100.57 million.

As a result of the decline, NII Holdings Inc. now has a market cap of $59.65 million.  In the last 
year, shares of NII Holdings Inc. have traded between a range of $3.63 and $0.36, and its 50-day SMA is currently $0.63 and 200-day SMA is $1.75. 


For a complete fundamental analysis of NII Holdings Inc., check out Equities.com’s Stock Valuation Analysis report for 
NIHD.

Want to invest with the experts? Subscribe to Equities Premium newsletters today! Visit http://www.equitiespremium.com/ to 
learn more about Guild Investment’s Market Commentary  and Adam Sarhan’s 
Find Leading Stocks  today. 

NII Holdings Inc is a provider of telecom services. The Company's services include mobile telephone voice service, push-to-talk services, wireless data services, business solutions and voice and data roaming services.

NII Holdings Inc. is based out of Reston, VA and has some 2,645 employees. Its CEO is Steven M. Shindler.

NII Holdings Inc. is a component of the Russell 2000. The Russell 2000 is one of the leading indices tracking small-cap companies in the United States. It's maintained by  Russell Investments, an 
industry leader in creating and maintaining indices, and consists of the smallest 2000 stocks from the broader Russell 3000 index.


    Russell's indices differ from traditional indices like the Dow Jones Industrial Average (DJIA) or S&P 500, whose members are selected by committee, because they base membership entirely on an 
objective, rules based methodology. The 3,000 largest companies by market cap make up the Russell 3000, with the 2,000 smaller companies making up the Russell 2000. It's a simple approach that gives 
a broad, unbiased look at the small-cap market as a whole.


To get more information on NII Holdings Inc. and to follow the company’s latest updates, you can visit the company’s profile page here:  
NIHD’s Profile. For more news on the financial markets and emerging growth companies, be sure to visit Equities.com’s 
Newsdesk. Also, don’t forget to sign-up for our daily 
email newsletter to ensure you don’t miss out on any of our best stories. 

