            NII Holdings, formerly known as Nextel International, is one of the world's leading providers of fully integrated wireless communication services designed to meet the needs of business customers in selected international markets. Principal operations are in major business centers and related transportation corridors of Argentina, Brazil, Mexico and Peru. As part of NII's growth strategy, it has recently expanded wireless coverage in Latin America by purchasing companies with analog specialized mobile radio licenses in Chile. Using a proven technology, significant product differentiation and a business plan proven by Nextel Communications in the United States, NII Holdings has already begun to produce promising results in Latin America.
          






















